         <abstract>
            <p>This paper develops techniques to estimate dollar losses from non-tradable risks used in advanced finance classes. An Excel model is developed that simulates the frequency and severity of potential losses. The types of frequency and severity distributions are investigated and selection criteria discussed. The analytical closed-form formulae for an aggregate loss function generated by combining the frequency and severity distribution are provided as well. The simulated results are then compared to the analytical results. The advantages and disadvantages of using simulation software are also discussed.</p>
         </abstract>
